dc_title_s: Adams County, Iowa, 1966, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BJU. Form of individual image numbering: BJU-1GG-[number], BJU-2GG-[number], or BJU-3GG-[number]. "Year Flown 1966". Flown by Park Aerial Surveys, Inc. Louisville, K.Y. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
dc_publisher_s: United States. Agricultural Stabilization and Conservation Service
